4. EXPERIMENTS
4.1 Data Collection
Dataset of 46 Facebook users‚Äô privacy settings is obtained by questionnaire. The users‚Äô profiles items and interactive documents in one month are downloaded from Facebook website. The items of user privacy settings include gender, birth date, phone number, education, current city, hometown, life events, professional skill, college. Friendship between 46 users is shown as Figure 4.
4.2 Experiments and Results
4.2.1 Experiment 1
In this experiment, the IPLP of 46 users is shown as Figure 5. The user with the higher IPLP more likely divulges the privacy of friends online. From Figure 5, the result that users numbered 44 and 45 are more vulnerable in divulging others‚Äô privacy is obtained, attributed to the number of friends belonged to target users and various evaluation of numerous friends with high PPA.

